A YEAR-LONG, $160m expedition to the Arctic has passed its halfway mark and is amassing sobering data about the effects of climate change there. One of the scientists on board explains the discoveries so far. Also, Peter Schwartz, who imagined the future in Minority Report, shares his advice for forward planning in the age of covid-19. And, what next for facial recognition technology? Runtime: 25 min  Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify |Google | Stitcher | TuneIn Please subscribe to The Economist for full access to print, digital and audio editions: www.economist.com/podcastoffer